This paper discusses the optimization of Lattice Boltzmann methods, which are commonly used in computational fluid dynamics. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science). The paper also discusses performance optimization on modern hardware, which could fall under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). Additionally, the paper mentions a variety of implementation options, which could fall under cs.SE (Software Engineering). The paper also establishes a performance model for each kernel, which could fall under cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). Finally, the paper discusses a comparison of implementations and recent architectures, which could fall under cs.MS (Mathematical Software).
